obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (7798)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7798&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Private Security`
  line `Agencies (Regulation) Act, 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019)..`
  line
  line `2. 14th March, 2006, vide notification No. S.O. 317(E), dated 15th March, 2006, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (7799)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7799&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "armoured car service" means the service provided by deployment of armed guards along`
  line `with armoured car and such other related services which may be notified by the Central Government`
  line `or as the case may be, the State Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(b) "Controlling Authority" means the Controlling Authority appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "licence" means a licence granted under sub-section (5) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "private security" means security provided by a person, other than a public servant, to protect`
  line `or guard any person or property or both and includes provision of armoured car service;`
  line
  line `(g) "private security agency" means a person or body of persons other than a government agency,`
  line `department or organisation engaged in the business of providing private security services including`
  line `training to private security guards or their supervisor or providing private security guards to any`
  line `industrial or business undertaking or a company or any other person or property;`
  line
  line `(h) "private security guard" means a person providing private security with or without arms to`
  line `another person or property or both and includes a supervisor;`
  line
  line `(i) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, includes the Administrator of that Union`
  line `territory appointed by the President under article 239 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (7800)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment of Controlling Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7800&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification,`
  line `designate an officer not below the rank of a Joint Secretary in the Home Department of the State or an`
  line `equivalent officer to be the Controlling Authority for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, for efficient discharge of functions by the Controlling Authority,`
  line `provide it with such other officers and staff as that Government considers necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (7801)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Persons or Private Security Agency not to engage or provide private security guard without licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7801&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No person shall carry on or commence the business of private security agency, unless he holds`
  line `a licence issued under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person carrying on the business of private security agency, immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, may continue to do so for a period of one year from the date of such`
  line `commencement and if he has made an application for such licence within the said period of one year, till`
  line `the disposal of such application:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no private security agency shall provide private security abroad without`
  line `obtaining permission of the Controlling Authority, which shall consult the Central Government before`
  line `according such permission.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (7802)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Eligibility for licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7802&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `An application for issue of a licence under this Act shall only be`
  line `considered from a person after due verification of his antecedents.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (7803)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Persons not eligible for licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7803&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be considered for issue of a licence under`
  line `this Act, if he has been—`
  line
  line `(a) convicted of an offence in connection with promotion, formation or management of a`
  line `company (any fraud or misfeasance committed by him in relation to the company), including an`
  line `undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) convicted by a competent court for an offence, the prescribed punishment for which is`
  line `imprisonment of not less than two years; or`
  line
  line `(c) keeping links with any organisation or association which is banned under any law on account`
  line `of their activities which pose threat to national security or public order or there is information about`
  line `such a person indulging in activities which are prejudicial to national security or public order; or`
  line
  line `(d) dismissed or removed from Government service on grounds of misconduct or moral turpitude.`
  line
  line `(2) A company, firm or an association of persons shall not be considered for issue of a licence under`
  line `this Act, if, it is not registered in India, or having a proprietor or a majority shareholder, partner or`
  line `director, who is not a citizen of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (7804)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Application for grant of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7804&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for grant of licence to a private security`
  line `agency shall be made to the Controlling Authority in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The applicant shall submit an affidavit incorporating the details in relation to the provisions`
  line `contained in section 6, ensure the availability of the training for its private security guards and supervisors`
  line `required under sub-section (2) of section 9, fulfilment of conditions under section 11 and of cases`
  line `registered with police or pending in a court of law involving the applicant.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by a fee of—`
  line
  line `(a) rupees five thousand if the private security agency is operating in one district of a State;`
  line
  line `(b) rupees ten thousand if the agency is operating in more than one but up to five districts of a`
  line `State; and`
  line
  line `(c) rupees twenty-five thousand if it is operating in the whole State.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Controlling Authority may, after making`
  line `such inquiries as it considers necessary and obtaining no objection certificate from the concerned police`
  line `authority, by order in writing, either grant a licence or refuse to grant the same within a period of sixty`
  line `days from the date of receipt of application with complete particulars and the prescribed fee:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of refusal shall be made unless—`
  line
  line `(a) the applicant has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard; and`
  line
  line `(b) the grounds on which licence is refused is mentioned in the order.`
  line
  line `(5) A licence granted under this section—`
  line
  line `(a) shall be valid for a period of five years unless the same is cancelled under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13;`
  line
  line `(b) may be renewed from time to time after the expiry of five years, for a further period of five`
  line `years on payment of such fee as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(c) shall be subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (7805)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Renewal of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7805&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for renewal of licence shall be made to the Controlling`
  line `Authority, not less than forty-five days before the date of expiry of the period of validity thereof, in suchform as may be prescribed and shall be accompanied by the requisite fee and other documents required`
  line `under sections 6, 7 and 11 of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controlling Authority shall pass an order on application for renewal of licence within thirty`
  line `days from the date of receipt of application complete in all respects.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Controlling Authority may, after making`
  line `such inquiries as he considers necessary and by order in writing, renew the licence or refuse to renew the`
  line `same:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of refusal shall be made except after giving the applicant a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (7806)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Conditions for commencement of operation and engagement of supervisors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7806&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `private security agency shall, within six months of obtaining the licence, commence its activities.`
  line
  line `(2) Every private security agency shall ensure imparting of such training and skills to its private`
  line `security guards and supervisors as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person carrying on the business of private security agency, before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, shall ensure the required training to its security guards and supervisors within`
  line `a period of one year from the date of such commencement.`
  line
  line `(3) Every private security agency shall, within sixty days from the date of issue of the licence, employ`
  line `such number of supervisors, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) A private security agency shall not employ or engage a person as a supervisor unless he fulfils the`
  line `conditions specified in sub-section (1) of section 10.`
  line
  line `(5) While engaging a supervisor of private security guards, every private security agency shall give`
  line `preference to a person who has experience of serving in the Army, Navy, Air Force or any other Armed`
  line `forces of the Union or State Police including armed constabularies and Home Guards for a period of not`
  line `less than three years.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (7807)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Eligibility to be a private security guard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7807&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) A private security agency shall not employ or`
  line `engage any person as a private security guard unless he—`
  line
  line `(a) is a citizen of India or a citizen of such other country as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify;`
  line
  line `(b) has completed eighteen years of age but has not attained the age of sixty-five years;`
  line
  line `(c) satisfies the agency about his character and antecedents in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(d) has completed the prescribed security training successfully;`
  line
  line `(e) fulfils such physical standards as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(f) satisfies such other conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No person who has been convicted by a competent court or who has been dismissed or removed`
  line `on grounds of misconduct or moral turpitude while serving in any of the armed forces of the Union, State`
  line `Police Organisations, Central or State Governments or in any private security agency shall be employed`
  line `or engaged as a private security guard or a supervisor.`
  line
  line `(3) Every private security agency may, while employing a person as a private security guard, give`
  line `preference to a person who has served as a member in one or more of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Army;`
  line
  line `(ii) Navy;`
  line
  line `(iii) Air Force;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other armed forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(v) Police, including armed constabularies of States; and`
  line
  line `(vi) Home Guards.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (7808)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Conditions of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7808&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may frame rules to prescribe the conditions`
  line `on which licence shall be granted under this Act and such conditions shall include requirements as to the`
  line `training which the licensee is to undergo, details of the person or persons forming the agency, obligation`
  line `as to the information to be provided from time to time to the Controlling Authority regarding any change`
  line `in their address, change of management and also about any criminal charge made against them in the`
  line `course of their performance of duties of the private security agency or as the case may be, a private`
  line `security guard employed or engaged by them.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may make provision in the rules to verify about imparting of required`
  line `training by the private security agency under sub-section (2) of section 9 and to review continuation or`
  line `otherwise of licence of such private security agency which may not have adhered to the condition of`
  line `ensuring the required training.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (7809)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Licence to be exhibited.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7809&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Every private security agency shall exhibit its licence or copy thereof`
  line `in a conspicuous place of its business.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (7810)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Cancellation and suspension of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7810&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controlling Authority may cancel any licence`
  line `on any one or more of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the licence has been obtained on misrepresentation or suppression of material facts;`
  line
  line `(b) that the licence holder has used false documents or photographs;`
  line
  line `(c) that the licence holder has violated the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder or`
  line `any of the conditions of the licence;`
  line
  line `(d) that the licence holder has misused information obtained by him during the discharge of his`
  line `duties as the private security agency to any industrial or business undertaking or a company or any`
  line `other person;`
  line
  line `(e) that the licence holder by using any letter-head, advertisement or any other printed matter or`
  line `in any other manner represented that the private security agency is an instrumentality of the`
  line `Government or such agency is or has been using a name different from that for which licence has`
  line `been granted;`
  line
  line `(f) that the licence holder is or has been impersonating or permitting or aiding or abetting any`
  line `body to impersonate as a public servant;`
  line
  line `(g) that the private security agency had failed to commence its activities or to engage a supervisor`
  line `within the specified time period;`
  line
  line `(h) that the licence holder is or has wilfully failed or refused to render the services agreed to any`
  line person;
  line
  line `(i) that the licence holder has done any act which is in violation of a court order or an order of a`
  line `lawful authority or is or has been advising, encouraging or assisting any person to violate any such`
  line order;
  line
  line `(j) that the licence holder has violated the provisions of the Acts given in the Schedule which may`
  line `be modified by the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(k) that there have been repeated instances when the private security guard or guards provided by`
  line `the private security agency--`
  line
  line `(i) failed to provide private security or were guilty of gross negligence in not providing such`
  line security;
  line
  line `(ii) committed a breach of trust or misappropriated the property or a part thereof which they`
  line `were supposed to protect;`
  line
  line `(iii) were found habitually drunk or indisciplined;`
  line
  line `(iv) were found to be involved in committing crimes; or`
  line
  line `(v) had connived or abetted a crime against the person or property placed under their charge;`
  line or
  line
  line `(l) that the licence holder has done any act which poses a threat to national security, or did not`
  line `provide assistance to the police or other authority in the discharge of its duties or acted in a manner`
  line `prejudicial to national security or public order or law and order.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Controlling Authority, for reasons to be recorded in writing, is satisfied that pending`
  line `the question of cancelling of licence on any of the grounds mentioned in sub-section (1), it is necessary to`
  line `do so, that Controlling Authority may, by order in writing, suspend the operation of the licence for such`
  line `period not exceeding thirty days as may be specified in the order and require the licence holder to show`
  line `cause, within fifteen days from the date of issue of such order, as to why the suspension of the licence`
  line `should not be extended till the determination of the question of cancellation.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order of suspending or cancelling of a licence shall be in writing and shall specify the`
  line `reasons for such suspension or cancellation and a copy thereof shall be communicated to the person`
  line affected.
  line
  line `(4) No order of cancellation of licence under sub-section (1) shall be made unless the person`
  line `concerned has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (7811)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7811&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Controlling Authority refusing the licence`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 7 or renewal under sub-section (3) of section 8 or order of suspension of`
  line `licence under sub-section (2) of section 13 or cancellation of licence under sub-section (1) of that section,`
  line `may prefer an appeal against that order to the Home Secretary of the State Government within a period of`
  line `sixty days of the date of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the said period of sixty days if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the State Government that he has sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within`
  line `that period.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a copy of the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(3) Before disposing of an appeal, the State Government shall give the appellant a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (7812)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Register to be maintained by a private security agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7812&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every private security agency`
  line `shall maintain a register containing—`
  line
  line `(a) the names and addresses of the persons managing the private security agency;`
  line
  line `(b) the names, addresses, photographs and salaries of the private security guards and supervisors`
  line `under its control;`
  line
  line `(c) the names and addresses of the persons whom it had provided private security guards or`
  line `services; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controlling Authority may call for such information as it considers necessary from any`
  line `private security agency, supervisor or private security guard to ensure due compliance of the Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (7813)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Inspection of licence, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7813&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Controlling Authority or any other officer authorised by it in this`
  line `behalf may at any reasonable time, enter the premises of the private security agency and inspect and`
  line `examine the place of business, the records, accounts and other documents connected with the licence and`
  line `may take copy of any document.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (7814)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Issue of photo identity card.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7814&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every private security guard shall be issued a photo identity`
  line `card, by the private security agency employing or engaging the guard.`
  line
  line `(2) The photo identity card under sub-section (1) shall be issued in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every private security guard or supervisor shall carry on his person the photo identity card issued`
  line `under sub-section (1) and shall produce it on demand for inspection by the Controlling Authority or any`
  line `other officer authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (7815)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Disclosure of information to unauthorised person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7815&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who may be or has been`
  line `employed or engaged as a private security guard by the private security agency shall not divulge to anyone other than the employer, or in such manner and to such person as the employer directs, any`
  line `information acquired by him during such employment with respect to the work which he has been`
  line `assigned by such employer, except such disclosure as may be required under this Act or in connection`
  line `with any inquiry or investigation by the police or as may be required by an authority or process of law.`
  line
  line `(2) All private security guards of a private security agency shall render necessary assistance to the`
  line `police or to such authority in the process of any investigation pertaining to the activities of that agency.`
  line
  line `(3) If violation of any law is noticed by any private security guard during the course of discharge of`
  line `his duties, he shall bring it to the notice of his superior, who in turn shall inform the police either through`
  line `his employer or agency or on his own`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (7816)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7816&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification, direct that any power or function`
  line `(except the powers to make rules under section 25)—`
  line
  line `(a) which may be exercised or performed by it, or`
  line
  line `(b) which may be exercised or performed by the Controlling Authority,`
  line
  line `under this Act, may, in relation to such matter and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified`
  line `in the notification, be also exercised or performed by such officer or authority subordinate to the`
  line `Government or officer subordinate to the Controlling Authority, as may be specified in such notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (7817)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Punishment for contravention of certain provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7817&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who contravenes the`
  line `provisions of section 4 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year,`
  line `or with fine which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person or private security agency who contravenes, the provisions of sections 9, 10 and 12 of`
  line `the Act, shall be punishable with a fine which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees, in addition to`
  line `suspension or cancellation of the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (7818)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Penalty for unauthorised use of certain uniforms.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7818&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If any private security guard or supervisor`
  line `wears the uniform of the Army, Air force, Navy or any other armed forces of the Union or Police or any`
  line `dress having the appearance or bearing any of the distinctive marks of that uniform, he and the proprietor`
  line `of the private security agency shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one`
  line `year or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (7819)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7819&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section—`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (7820)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Indemnity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7820&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Controlling`
  line `authority or any other officer authorised by it in respect of anything in good faith done or intended to be`
  line `done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (7821)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Framing of model rules for adoption by States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7821&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may frame model`
  line `rules in respect of all or any of the matters with respect to which the State Government may make rules under this Act, and where any such model rules have been framed the State Government shall, while`
  line `making any rules in respect of that matter under section 25, so far as is practicable, conform to such`
  line `model rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (7822)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940&sectionId=7822&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00022_200529_1517807325940
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure for verification of character and antecedents under clause (c) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 10; the type of training under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 10; the physical`
  line `standard under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 10; and other conditions under clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of supervisors to be employed under sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) the form of an application for grant of licence under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which the licence to be granted under sub-section (4) of section 7 and conditions`
  line `subject to which such licence to be granted under section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of an application for renewal of licence under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) the form under sub-section (2) of section 14 for preferring an appeal;`
  line
  line `(g) particulars to be maintained in a register under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which photo identity card under sub-section (2) of section 17 be issued;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
  line
  line `(4) In respect of Union territories, every rule made to carry out the provisions of the Act shall be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament and where there exists a Legislative Assembly, before that Assembly`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
